#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pi-tv-bu-vb-pc46"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:0.4"
msgid "Acelakavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 46"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:0.5"
msgid "46. Cārittasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on visiting"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.98, pts-cs-bu-pc46.1, pts-vp-en.2.362, ms2V_932 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa upaṭṭhākakulaṃ āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ bhattena nimantesi."
msgstr "At that time a family that was supporting Venerable Upananda the Sakyan had invited him to a meal,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.3"
msgid "Aññepi bhikkhū bhattena nimantesi."
msgstr "and they had invited other monks too."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.4"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto purebhattaṃ, kulāni payirupāsati."
msgstr "But since Upananda was visiting other families before that meal,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.5"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū te manusse etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "the other monks said to that family,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.6"
msgid "“dethāvuso, bhattan”ti."
msgstr "“Please, give the meal.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.7"
msgid "“Āgametha, bhante, yāvāyyo upanando āgacchatī”ti."
msgstr "“Please wait, Venerables, until Venerable Upananda arrives.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.8"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho te bhikkhū … pe …"
msgstr "A second time …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.9"
msgid "tatiyampi kho te bhikkhū te manusse etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "A third time those monks said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.10"
msgid "“dethāvuso, bhattaṃ; pure kālo atikkamatī”ti."
msgstr "“Please give the meal before the time for eating comes to an end.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.11"
msgid "“Yampi mayaṃ, bhante, bhattaṃ karimhā ayyassa upanandassa kāraṇā."
msgstr "“But, Venerables, we made the meal because of Venerable Upananda."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.12"
msgid "Āgametha, bhante, yāvāyyo upanando āgacchatī”ti."
msgstr "Please wait until he arrives.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_933 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.13"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto purebhattaṃ kulāni payirupāsitvā divā āgacchati."
msgstr "Then, after visiting those families, Upananda arrived late,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.14"
msgid "Bhikkhū na cittarūpaṃ bhuñjiṃsu."
msgstr "and those monks did not eat as much as they had intended."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.15"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.16"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.17"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjissatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda visit families first when invited to a meal?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.18"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.363 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.19"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.20"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.21"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjissasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you visit families first when invited to a meal?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.22"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.23"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.23a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule">
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_934
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.24"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk who has been invited to a meal visits families beforehand, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p>
#. REF: sc4, ms2V_935 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:1.25"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-pli4.99, pts-cs-bu-pc46.2, ms2V_936 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa upaṭṭhākakulaṃ saṃghassatthāya khādanīyaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards a family that was supporting Upananda sent non-staple food to the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.2"
msgid "“ayyassa upanandassa dassetvā saṃghassa dātabban”ti."
msgstr "They gave instructions that the food should be shown to Upananda and then given to the Order."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto gāmaṃ piṇḍāya paviṭṭho hoti."
msgstr "Just then Upananda had entered the village for alms."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.3"
msgid "Atha kho te manussā ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhū pucchiṃsu—"
msgstr "When those people arrived at the monastery,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.4"
msgid "“kahaṃ, bhante, ayyo upanando”ti?"
msgstr "they asked for Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.5"
msgid "“Esāvuso, āyasmā upanando sakyaputto gāmaṃ piṇḍāya paviṭṭho”ti."
msgstr "and they were told where he was."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.6"
msgid "“Idaṃ, bhante, khādanīyaṃ ayyassa upanandassa dassetvā saṃghassa dātabban”ti."
msgstr "They said, “Venerables, after showing it to Venerable Upananda, this non-staple food is to be given to the Order.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.7"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "The monks told the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.8"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "who then gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.9"
msgid "“tena hi, bhikkhave, paṭiggahetvā nikkhipatha yāva upanando āgacchatī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, monks, receive it and put it aside until Upananda returns.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_937, pts-vp-en.2.364 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.10"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto—“bhagavatā paṭikkhittaṃ purebhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjitun”ti pacchābhattaṃ kulāni payirupāsitvā divā paṭikkami, khādanīyaṃ ussāriyittha."
msgstr "Knowing that the Master had prohibited visiting families before the meal, Upananda visited them after the meal instead. As a consequence he returned late to the monastery, and the food had to be returned to the donors."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.11"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.12"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.13"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto pacchābhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjissatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda visit families after the meal?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.14"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, pacchābhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you do this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.15"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.16"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.17"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, pacchābhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjissasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you visit families after the meal?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.18"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.19"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.19a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule">
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_938
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.20"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk who has been invited to a meal visits families beforehand or afterwards, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_939 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:2.21"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Third sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc9, pts-cs-bu-pc46.3, ms2V_940 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:3.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū cīvaradānasamaye kukkuccāyantā kulāni na payirupāsanti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards it was the robe-giving season. But being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not visit families."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:3.2"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ parittaṃ uppajjati."
msgstr "As a result they only obtained a small amount of robe-cloth."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:3.3"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. HTML: <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:3.4"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvaradānasamaye kulāni payirupāsituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to visit families during the robe-giving season."

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:3.5"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:3.5a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Third preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule">
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_941 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:3.6"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjeyya, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk who has been invited to a meal visits families beforehand or afterwards, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:3.7"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reason is this:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:3.8"
msgid "Cīvaradānasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "it is the robe-giving season.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc11, ms2V_942 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:3.9"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:4.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Fourth sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc12, pts-cs-bu-pc46.4, ms2V_943, pts-vp-en.2.365 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:4.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū cīvarakammaṃ karonti, attho ca hoti sūciyāpi suttenapi satthakenapi."
msgstr "Soon afterwards the monks were making a robe, and they needed a needle, thread, and scissors."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:4.2"
msgid "Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā kulāni na payirupāsanti."
msgstr "But being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not visit families."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:4.3"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. HTML: <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:4.4"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvarakārasamaye kulāni payirupāsituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to visit families if you are making a robe."

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:4.5"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:4.5a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Fourth preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule">
#. REF: sc13, pts-vp-pli4.100, ms2V_944
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:4.6"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjeyya, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk who has been invited to a meal visits families beforehand or afterwards, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:4.7"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:4.8"
msgid "Cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "it is the robe-giving season, he is making a robe.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc14, ms2V_945 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:4.9"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:5.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Fifth sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc15, pts-cs-bu-pc46.5, ms2V_946 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:5.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū gilānā honti, attho ca hoti bhesajjehi."
msgstr "Soon afterwards there were sick monks who needed medicines."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:5.2"
msgid "Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā kulāni na payirupāsanti."
msgstr "But being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not visit families."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:5.3"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. HTML: <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:5.4"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, santaṃ bhikkhuṃ āpucchā kulāni payirupāsituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to visit families after informing an available monk."

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:5.5"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:5.5a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule">
#. REF: sc16, ms2V_947
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:5.6"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu nimantito sabhatto samāno santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjeyya, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk who has been invited to a meal visits families beforehand or afterwards without informing an available monk, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:5.7"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:5.8"
msgid "Cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "it is the robe-giving season, he is making a robe.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc17, pts-cs-bu-pc46.6.1, ms2V_948
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc18, pts-vp-en.2.366, ms2V_949
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.6"
msgid "Nimantito nāma"
msgstr "Invited:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.7"
msgid "pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññatarena bhojanena nimantito."
msgstr "invited to eat any of the five staple foods."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc19, ms2V_950
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.8"
msgid "Sabhatto nāma"
msgstr "To a meal:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.9"
msgid "yena nimantito tena sabhatto."
msgstr "the invitation includes a meal."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc20, ms2V_951
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.10"
msgid "Santaṃ nāma"
msgstr "An available monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.11"
msgid "bhikkhuṃ sakkā hoti āpucchā pavisituṃ."
msgstr "he is able to inform and then enter."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc21, ms2V_952
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.12"
msgid "Asantaṃ nāma"
msgstr "No available monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.13"
msgid "bhikkhuṃ na sakkā hoti āpucchā pavisituṃ."
msgstr "he is not able to inform and then enter."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc22, ms2V_953
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.14"
msgid "Purebhattaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Beforehand:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.15"
msgid "yena nimantito taṃ abhuttāvī."
msgstr "he has not yet eaten what he has been invited to eat."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. VAR: kusaggenapi → aruṇuggamanepi (bj)
#. REF: sc23, ms2V_954
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.16"
msgid "Pacchābhattaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Afterwards:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.17"
msgid "yena nimantito taṃ antamaso kusaggenapi bhuttaṃ hoti."
msgstr "even if he has just eaten what fits on the tip of a blade of grass from what he has been invited to eat."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc24, ms2V_955
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.18"
msgid "Kulaṃ nāma"
msgstr "A family:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.19"
msgid "cattāri kulāni—"
msgstr "there are four kinds of families:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.20"
msgid "khattiyakulaṃ, brāhmaṇakulaṃ, vessakulaṃ, suddakulaṃ."
msgstr "aristocratic families, brahmin families, merchant families, worker families."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc25, ms2V_956
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.21"
msgid "Kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjeyyāti"
msgstr "Visits families:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.22"
msgid "aññassa gharūpacāraṃ okkamantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "if he enters the vicinity of someone else’s house, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.23"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ ummāraṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he crosses the threshold with the first foot, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.24"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he crosses the threshold with the second foot, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc26, ms2V_957
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.25"
msgid "Aññatra samayāti"
msgstr "Unless there is an appropriate reason:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.26"
msgid "ṭhapetvā samayaṃ."
msgstr "except at an appropriate time."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc27, ms2V_958
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.27"
msgid "Cīvaradānasamayo nāma"
msgstr "It is the robe-giving season:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
# NOTE: That is, the last month of the rainy season plus the four months of the cold season.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.28"
msgid "anatthate kathine vassānassa pacchimo māso, atthate kathine pañca māsā."
msgstr "for one who has not done the robe-making ceremony, it is the last month of the rainy season. For one who has done the robe-making ceremony, it is the five-month period."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc28, ms2V_959
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.29"
msgid "Cīvarakārasamayo nāma"
msgstr "He is making a robe:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.1.30"
msgid "cīvare kayiramāne."
msgstr "when he is making a robe."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc29, pts-cs-bu-pc46.6.2, ms2V_960 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.2.1"
msgid "Nimantite nimantitasaññī santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjati, aññatra samayā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he has been invited, and he perceives that he has, and he visits families beforehand or afterwards without informing an available monk, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.2.2"
msgid "Nimantite vematiko santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjati, aññatra samayā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he has been invited, but he is unsure if he has, and he visits families beforehand or afterwards without informing an available monk, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.367 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.2.3"
msgid "Nimantite animantitasaññī santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjati, aññatra samayā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he has been invited, but he does not perceives that he has, and he visits families beforehand or afterwards without informing an available monk, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc30, pts-vp-pli4.101, ms2V_961 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.2.4"
msgid "Animantite nimantitasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he has not been invited, but he perceives that he has, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.2.5"
msgid "Animantite vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he has not been invited,  but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.2.6"
msgid "Animantite animantitasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If he has not been invited, and he does not perceive that he has, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc31, pts-cs-bu-pc46.6.3, ms2V_962 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.3.2"
msgid "samaye,"
msgstr "if there is an appropriate reason;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.3.3"
msgid "santaṃ bhikkhuṃ āpucchā pavisati,"
msgstr "if he enters after informing an available monk;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.3.4"
msgid "asantaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā pavisati,"
msgstr "if, when there is no available monk, he enters without informing;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.3.5"
msgid "aññassa gharena maggo hoti,"
msgstr "if the road passes someone else’s house;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.3.6"
msgid "gharūpacārena maggo hoti,"
msgstr "if the road passes the vicinity of someone else’s house;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.3.7"
msgid "antarārāmaṃ gacchati,"
msgstr "if he is going between monasteries;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.3.8"
msgid "bhikkhunupassayaṃ gacchati,"
msgstr "if he is going to the dwelling place of nuns;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.3.9"
msgid "titthiyaseyyaṃ gacchati,"
msgstr "if he is going to the dwelling place of the ascetics of another sect;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.3.10"
msgid "paṭikkamanaṃ gacchati,"
msgstr "if he is returning to the monastery;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.3.11"
msgid "bhattiyagharaṃ gacchati,"
msgstr "if he is going to a house for a meal;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.3.12"
msgid "āpadāsu,"
msgstr "if there are dangers;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.3.13"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.3.14"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc32, ms2V_963 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:6.3.15"
msgid "Cārittasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "The sixth rule, the training rule on visiting, is finished."
